151  int bufferLength;
152 
153  int charOctetLength;

167  String typeName;
168 
169  TypeDescriptor(String typeInfo, String nullabilityInfo)
170  throws SQLException {
171  if (typeInfo == null) {
172  throw SQLError.createSQLException("NULL typeinfo not supported.",
173  SQLError.SQL_STATE_ILLEGAL_ARGUMENT, getExceptionInterceptor());
174  }
175 
176  String mysqlType = "";
177  String fullMysqlType = null;
178 
179  if (typeInfo.indexOf("(") != -1) {
180  mysqlType = typeInfo.substring(0, typeInfo.indexOf("("));
181  } else {
182  mysqlType = typeInfo;
183  }
184 
185  int indexOfUnsignedInMysqlType = StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(
186  mysqlType, "unsigned");
187 
188  if (indexOfUnsignedInMysqlType != -1) {
189  mysqlType = mysqlType.substring(0,
190  (indexOfUnsignedInMysqlType - 1));
191  }
192 
193  // Add unsigned to typename reported to enduser as 'native type', if
194  // present
195 
196  boolean isUnsigned = false;
197 
198  if ((StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "unsigned") != -1) &&
199  (StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "set") != 0) &&
200  (StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "enum") != 0)) {
201  fullMysqlType = mysqlType + " unsigned";
202  isUnsigned = true;
203  } else {
204  fullMysqlType = mysqlType;
205  }
206 
207  if (conn.getCapitalizeTypeNames()) {
208  fullMysqlType = fullMysqlType.toUpperCase(Locale.ENGLISH);
209  }
210 
211  this.dataType = (short) MysqlDefs.mysqlToJavaType(mysqlType);
212 
213  this.typeName = fullMysqlType;
214 
215  // Figure Out the Size
216 
217  if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "enum")) {
218  String temp = typeInfo.substring(typeInfo.indexOf("("),
219  typeInfo.lastIndexOf(")"));
220  java.util.StringTokenizer tokenizer = new java.util.StringTokenizer(
221  temp, ",");
222  int maxLength = 0;
223 
224  while (tokenizer.hasMoreTokens()) {
225  maxLength = Math.max(maxLength, (tokenizer.nextToken()
226  .length() - 2));
227  }
228 
229  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(maxLength);
230  this.decimalDigits = null;
231  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "set")) {
232  String temp = typeInfo.substring(typeInfo.indexOf("(") + 1,
233  typeInfo.lastIndexOf(")"));
234  java.util.StringTokenizer tokenizer = new java.util.StringTokenizer(
235  temp, ",");
236  int maxLength = 0;
237 
238  int numElements = tokenizer.countTokens();
239 
240  if (numElements > 0) {
241  maxLength += (numElements - 1);
242  }
243 
244  while (tokenizer.hasMoreTokens()) {
245  String setMember = tokenizer.nextToken().trim();
246 
247  if (setMember.startsWith("'")
248  && setMember.endsWith("'")) {
249  maxLength += setMember.length() - 2;
250  } else {
251  maxLength += setMember.length();
252  }
253  }
254 
255  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(maxLength);
256  this.decimalDigits = null;
257  } else if (typeInfo.indexOf(",") != -1) {
258  // Numeric with decimals
259  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(typeInfo.substring((typeInfo
260  .indexOf("(") + 1), (typeInfo.indexOf(","))).trim());
261  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(typeInfo.substring(
262  (typeInfo.indexOf(",") + 1),
263  (typeInfo.indexOf(")"))).trim());
264  } else {
265  this.columnSize = null;
266  this.decimalDigits = null;
267 
268  /* If the size is specified with the DDL, use that */
269  if ((StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "char") != -1
270  || StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "text") != -1
271  || StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "blob") != -1
272  || StringUtils
273  .indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "binary") != -1 || StringUtils
274  .indexOfIgnoreCase(typeInfo, "bit") != -1)
275  && typeInfo.indexOf("(") != -1) {
276  int endParenIndex = typeInfo.indexOf(")");
277 
278  if (endParenIndex == -1) {
279  endParenIndex = typeInfo.length();
280  }
281 
282  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(typeInfo.substring(
283  (typeInfo.indexOf("(") + 1), endParenIndex).trim());
284 
285  // Adjust for pseudo-boolean
286  if (conn.getTinyInt1isBit()
287  && this.columnSize.intValue() == 1
288  && StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCase(typeInfo,
289  0, "tinyint")) {
290  if (conn.getTransformedBitIsBoolean()) {
291  this.dataType = Types.BOOLEAN;
292  this.typeName = "BOOLEAN";
293  } else {
294  this.dataType = Types.BIT;
295  this.typeName = "BIT";
296  }
297  }
298  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
299  "tinyint")) {
300  if (conn.getTinyInt1isBit() && typeInfo.indexOf("(1)") != -1) {
301  if (conn.getTransformedBitIsBoolean()) {
302  this.dataType = Types.BOOLEAN;
303  this.typeName = "BOOLEAN";
304  } else {
305  this.dataType = Types.BIT;
306  this.typeName = "BIT";
307  }
308  } else {
309  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(3);
310  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
311  }
312  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
313  "smallint")) {
314  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(5);
315  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
316  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
317  "mediumint")) {
318  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(isUnsigned ? 8 : 7);
319  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
320  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
321  "int")) {
322  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(10);
323  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
324  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
325  "integer")) {
326  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(10);
327  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
328  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
329  "bigint")) {
330  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(isUnsigned ? 20 : 19);
331  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
332  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
333  "int24")) {
334  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(19);
335  this.decimalDigits = Integer.valueOf(0);
336  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
337  "real")) {
338  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(12);
339  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
340  "float")) {
341  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(12);
342  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
343  "decimal")) {
344  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(12);
345  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
346  "numeric")) {
347  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(12);
348  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
349  "double")) {
350  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(22);
351  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
352  "char")) {
353  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(1);
354  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
355  "varchar")) {
356  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(255);
357  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
358  "timestamp")) {
359  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(19);
360  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
361  "datetime")) {
362  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(19);
363  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
364  "date")) {
365  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(10);
366  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
367  "time")) {
368  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(8);
369 
370  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
371  "tinyblob")) {
372  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(255);
373  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
374  "blob")) {
375  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(65535);
376  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
377  "mediumblob")) {
378  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(16777215);
379  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
380  "longblob")) {
381  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(Integer.MAX_VALUE);
382  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
383  "tinytext")) {
384  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(255);
385  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
386  "text")) {
387  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(65535);
388  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
389  "mediumtext")) {
390  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(16777215);
391  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
392  "longtext")) {
393  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(Integer.MAX_VALUE);
394  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
395  "enum")) {
396  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(255);
397  } else if (StringUtils.startsWithIgnoreCaseAndWs(typeInfo,
398  "set")) {
399  this.columnSize = Integer.valueOf(255);
400  }
401 
402  }
403 
404  // BUFFER_LENGTH
405  this.bufferLength = MysqlIO.getMaxBuf();
406 
407  // NUM_PREC_RADIX (is this right for char?)
408  this.numPrecRadix = 10;
409 
410  // Nullable?
411  if (nullabilityInfo != null) {
412  if (nullabilityInfo.equals("YES")) {
413  this.nullability = java.sql.DatabaseMetaData.columnNullable;
414  this.isNullable = "YES";
415 
416  } else if (nullabilityInfo.equals("UNKNOWN")) {
417  this.nullability = java.sql.DatabaseMetaData.columnNullableUnknown;
418  this.isNullable = "";
419 
420  // IS_NULLABLE
421  } else {
422  this.nullability = java.sql.DatabaseMetaData.columnNoNulls;
423  this.isNullable = "NO";
424  }
425  } else {
426  this.nullability = java.sql.DatabaseMetaData.columnNoNulls;
427  this.isNullable = "NO";
428  }
429  }

545

557  return false;

562  }
563 
564  if (!(obj instanceof ComparableWrapper<?, ?>)) {
565  return false;
566  }

570  }

898  static java.sql.ResultSet buildResultSet(com.mysql.jdbc.Field[] fields,
899  java.util.ArrayList<ResultSetRow> rows, MySQLConnection c) throws SQLException {
900  int fieldsLength = fields.length;
901 
902  for (int i = 0; i < fieldsLength; i++) {
903  int jdbcType = fields[i].getSQLType();
904 
905  switch (jdbcType) {
906  case Types.CHAR:
907  case Types.VARCHAR:
908  case Types.LONGVARCHAR:
909  fields[i].setCharacterSet(c.getCharacterSetMetadata());
910  break;
911  default:
912  // do nothing
913  }
914 
915  fields[i].setConnection(c);
916  fields[i].setUseOldNameMetadata(true);
917  }
918 
919  return com.mysql.jdbc.ResultSetImpl.getInstance(c.getCatalog(), fields,
920  new RowDataStatic(rows), c, null, false);
921  }

923  protected void convertToJdbcFunctionList(String catalog,
924  ResultSet proceduresRs, boolean needsClientFiltering, String db,
925  List<ComparableWrapper<String, ResultSetRow>> procedureRows, int nameIndex,
926  Field[] fields) throws SQLException {
927  while (proceduresRs.next()) {
928  boolean shouldAdd = true;
929 
930  if (needsClientFiltering) {
931  shouldAdd = false;
932 
933  String procDb = proceduresRs.getString(1);
934 
935  if (db == null && procDb == null) {
936  shouldAdd = true;
937  } else if (db != null && db.equals(procDb)) {
938  shouldAdd = true;
939  }
940  }
941 
942  if (shouldAdd) {
943  String functionName = proceduresRs.getString(nameIndex);
944 
945  byte[][] rowData = null;
946 
947  if (fields != null && fields.length == 9) {
948 
949  rowData = new byte[9][];
950  rowData[0] = catalog == null ? null : s2b(catalog); // PROCEDURE_CAT
951  rowData[1] = null; // PROCEDURE_SCHEM
952  rowData[2] = s2b(functionName); // PROCEDURE_NAME
953  rowData[3] = null; // reserved1
954  rowData[4] = null; // reserved2
955  rowData[5] = null; // reserved3
956  rowData[6] = s2b(proceduresRs.getString("comment")); // REMARKS
957  rowData[7] = s2b(Integer.toString(procedureReturnsResult)); // PROCEDURE_TYPE
958  rowData[8] = s2b(functionName);
959  } else {
960 
961  rowData = new byte[6][];
962 
963  rowData[0] = catalog == null ? null : s2b(catalog); // FUNCTION_CAT
964  rowData[1] = null; // FUNCTION_SCHEM
965  rowData[2] = s2b(functionName); // FUNCTION_NAME
966  rowData[3] = s2b(proceduresRs.getString("comment")); // REMARKS
967  rowData[4] = s2b(Integer.toString(getJDBC4FunctionNoTableConstant())); // FUNCTION_TYPE
968  rowData[5] = s2b(functionName); // SPECFIC NAME
969  }
970 
971  procedureRows.add(new ComparableWrapper<String, ResultSetRow>(functionName, new ByteArrayRow(rowData,
972  getExceptionInterceptor())));
973  }
974  }

1031  private ResultSetRow convertTypeDescriptorToProcedureRow(
1032  byte[] procNameAsBytes, byte[] procCatAsBytes, String paramName, boolean isOutParam,
1033  boolean isInParam, boolean isReturnParam, TypeDescriptor typeDesc,
1034  boolean forGetFunctionColumns,
1035  int ordinal)
1036  throws SQLException {
1037  byte[][] row = forGetFunctionColumns ? new byte[17][] : new byte[20][];
1038  row[0] = procCatAsBytes; // PROCEDURE_CAT
1039  row[1] = null; // PROCEDURE_SCHEM
1040  row[2] = procNameAsBytes; // PROCEDURE/NAME
1041  row[3] = s2b(paramName); // COLUMN_NAME
1042  row[4] = s2b(String.valueOf(getColumnType(isOutParam, isInParam, isReturnParam, forGetFunctionColumns))); // COLUMN_TYPE
1043  row[5] = s2b(Short.toString(typeDesc.dataType)); // DATA_TYPE
1044  row[6] = s2b(typeDesc.typeName); // TYPE_NAME
1045  row[7] = typeDesc.columnSize == null ? null : s2b(typeDesc.columnSize.toString()); // PRECISION
1046  row[8] = row[7]; // LENGTH
1047  row[9] = typeDesc.decimalDigits == null ? null : s2b(typeDesc.decimalDigits.toString()); // SCALE
1048  row[10] = s2b(Integer.toString(typeDesc.numPrecRadix)); // RADIX
1049  // Map 'column****' to 'procedure****'
1050  switch (typeDesc.nullability) {
1051  case columnNoNulls:
1052  row[11] = s2b(String.valueOf(procedureNoNulls)); // NULLABLE
1053  break;
1054 
1055  case columnNullable:
1056  row[11] = s2b(String.valueOf(procedureNullable)); // NULLABLE
1057  break;
1058 
1059  case columnNullableUnknown:
1060  row[11] = s2b(String.valueOf(procedureNullableUnknown)); // NULLABLE
1061  break;
1062 
1063  default:
1064  throw SQLError.createSQLException(
1065  "Internal error while parsing callable statement metadata (unknown nullability value fount)",
1066  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
1067  }
1068 
1069  row[12] = null;
1070 
1071  if (forGetFunctionColumns) {
1072  // CHAR_OCTECT_LENGTH
1073  row[13] = null;
1074 
1075  // ORDINAL_POSITION
1076  row[14] = s2b(String.valueOf(ordinal));
1077 
1078  // IS_NULLABLE
1079  row[15] = s2b(typeDesc.isNullable);
1080 
1081  // SPECIFIC_NAME
1082  row[16] = procNameAsBytes;
1083  } else {
1084  // COLUMN_DEF
1085  row[13] = null;
1086 
1087  // SQL_DATA_TYPE (future use)
1088  row[14] = null;
1089 
1090  // SQL_DATETIME_SUB (future use)
1091  row[15] = null;
1092 
1093  // CHAR_OCTET_LENGTH
1094  row[16] = null;
1095 
1096  // ORDINAL_POSITION
1097  row[17] = s2b(String.valueOf(ordinal));
1098 
1099  // IS_NULLABLE
1100  row[18] = s2b(typeDesc.isNullable);
1101 
1102  // SPECIFIC_NAME
1103  row[19] = procNameAsBytes;
1104  }
1105 
1106  return new ByteArrayRow(row, getExceptionInterceptor());
1107  }

1999  } else if (possibleParamName.equalsIgnoreCase("INOUT")) {
2000  isOutParam = true;
2001  isInParam = true;

2005  } else {
2006  throw SQLError.createSQLException(

2008  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
2009  }

2011  isOutParam = false;
2012  isInParam = true;
2013

2015  paramName = declarationTok.nextToken();
2016  } else {
2017  throw SQLError.createSQLException(
2018  "Internal error when parsing callable statement metadata (missing parameter name)",
2019  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
2020  }
2021  } else {
2022  isOutParam = false;
2023  isInParam = true;
2024 
2025  paramName = possibleParamName;
2026  }
2027 
2028  TypeDescriptor typeDesc = null;
2029 
2030  if (declarationTok.hasMoreTokens()) {
2031  StringBuffer typeInfoBuf = new StringBuffer(
2032  declarationTok.nextToken());
2033 
2034  while (declarationTok.hasMoreTokens()) {
2035  typeInfoBuf.append(" ");
2036  typeInfoBuf.append(declarationTok.nextToken());
2037  }
2038

2040 
2041  typeDesc = new TypeDescriptor(typeInfo, "YES");
2042  } else {
2043  throw SQLError.createSQLException(
2044  "Internal error when parsing callable statement metadata (missing parameter type)",
2045  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
2046  }
2047 
2048  if ((paramName.startsWith("`") && paramName.endsWith("`")) ||
2049  (isProcedureInAnsiMode && paramName.startsWith("\"") && paramName.endsWith("\""))) {
2050  paramName = paramName.substring(1, paramName.length() - 1);
2051  }
2052 
2053  int wildCompareRes = StringUtils.wildCompare(paramName,
2054  parameterNamePattern);
2055 
2056  if (wildCompareRes != StringUtils.WILD_COMPARE_NO_MATCH) {
2057  ResultSetRow row = convertTypeDescriptorToProcedureRow(
2058  procNameAsBytes, procCatAsBytes, paramName, isOutParam,
2059  isInParam, false, typeDesc, forGetFunctionColumns,
2060  ordinal++);
2061 
2062  resultRows.add(row);
2063  }
2064  } else {
2065  throw SQLError.createSQLException(
2066  "Internal error when parsing callable statement metadata (unknown output from 'SHOW CREATE PROCEDURE')",
2067  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
2068  }
2069  }
2070  } else {
2071  // Is this an error? JDBC spec doesn't make it clear if stored
2072  // procedure doesn't
2073  // exist, is it an error....
2074  }

2092  private int endPositionOfParameterDeclaration(int beginIndex,
2093  String procedureDef, String quoteChar) throws SQLException {

2096

2099  currentPos, procedureDef, ")", quoteChar.charAt(0),
2100  !this.conn.isNoBackslashEscapesSet());

2102  if (closedParenIndex != -1) {
2103  int nextOpenParenIndex = StringUtils
2104  .indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(currentPos,
2105  procedureDef, "(", quoteChar.charAt(0),
2106  !this.conn.isNoBackslashEscapesSet());

2109  && nextOpenParenIndex < closedParenIndex) {
2110  parenDepth++;
2111  currentPos = closedParenIndex + 1; // set after closed
2112  // paren that increases
2113  // depth
2114  } else {
2115  parenDepth--;
2116  currentPos = closedParenIndex; // start search from same
2117  // position
2118  }
2119  } else {

2121  throw SQLError

2124  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
2125  }

7070  public java.sql.ResultSet getVersionColumns(String catalog, String schema,
7071  final String table) throws SQLException {
7072 
7073  if (table == null) {
7074  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Table not specified.",
7075  SQLError.SQL_STATE_ILLEGAL_ARGUMENT, getExceptionInterceptor());
7076  }
7077 
7078  Field[] fields = new Field[8];
7079  fields[0] = new Field("", "SCOPE", Types.SMALLINT, 5);
7080  fields[1] = new Field("", "COLUMN_NAME", Types.CHAR, 32);
7081  fields[2] = new Field("", "DATA_TYPE", Types.INTEGER, 5);
7082  fields[3] = new Field("", "TYPE_NAME", Types.CHAR, 16);
7083  fields[4] = new Field("", "COLUMN_SIZE", Types.INTEGER, 16);
7084  fields[5] = new Field("", "BUFFER_LENGTH", Types.INTEGER, 16);
7085  fields[6] = new Field("", "DECIMAL_DIGITS", Types.SMALLINT, 16);
7086  fields[7] = new Field("", "PSEUDO_COLUMN", Types.SMALLINT, 5);
7087 
7088  final ArrayList<ResultSetRow> rows = new ArrayList<ResultSetRow>();
7089 
7090  final Statement stmt = this.conn.getMetadataSafeStatement();
7091 
7092  try {
7093 
7094  new IterateBlock<String>(getCatalogIterator(catalog)) {
7095  void forEach(String catalogStr) throws SQLException {
7096 
7097  ResultSet results = null;
7098  boolean with_where = conn.versionMeetsMinimum(5, 0, 0);
7099 
7100  try {
7101  StringBuffer whereBuf = new StringBuffer(" Extra LIKE '%on update CURRENT_TIMESTAMP%'");
7102  List<String> rsFields = new ArrayList<String>();
7103 
7104  // for versions prior to 5.1.23 we can get "on update CURRENT_TIMESTAMP"
7105  // only from SHOW CREATE TABLE
7106  if (!conn.versionMeetsMinimum(5, 1, 23)) {
7107 
7108  whereBuf = new StringBuffer();
7109  boolean firstTime = true;
7110 
7111  String query = new StringBuffer("SHOW CREATE TABLE ")
7112  .append(StringUtils.quoteIdentifier(catalogStr, conn.getPedantic())).append(".")
7113  .append(StringUtils.quoteIdentifier(table, conn.getPedantic())).toString();
7114 
7115  results = stmt.executeQuery(query);
7116  while (results.next()) {
7117  String createTableString = results.getString(2);
7118  StringTokenizer lineTokenizer = new StringTokenizer(createTableString, "\n");
7119 
7120  while (lineTokenizer.hasMoreTokens()) {
7121  String line = lineTokenizer.nextToken().trim();
7122  if (StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCase(line, "on update CURRENT_TIMESTAMP") > -1) {
7123  boolean usingBackTicks = true;
7124  int beginPos = line.indexOf(quotedId);
7125 
7126  if (beginPos == -1) {
7127  beginPos = line.indexOf("\"");
7128  usingBackTicks = false;
7129  }
7130 
7131  if (beginPos != -1) {
7132  int endPos = -1;
7133 
7134  if (usingBackTicks) {
7135  endPos = line.indexOf(quotedId, beginPos + 1);
7136  } else {
7137  endPos = line.indexOf("\"", beginPos + 1);
7138  }
7139 
7140  if (endPos != -1) {
7141  if (with_where) {
7142  if (!firstTime) {
7143  whereBuf.append(" or");
7144  } else {
7145  firstTime = false;
7146  }
7147  whereBuf.append(" Field='");
7148  whereBuf.append(line.substring(beginPos + 1, endPos));
7149  whereBuf.append("'");
7150  } else {
7151  rsFields.add(line.substring(beginPos + 1, endPos));
7152  }
7153  }
7154  }
7155  }
7156  }
7157  }
7158  }
7159 
7160  if (whereBuf.length() > 0 || rsFields.size() > 0) {
7161  StringBuffer queryBuf = new StringBuffer("SHOW ");
7162  queryBuf.append("COLUMNS FROM ");
7163  queryBuf.append(StringUtils.quoteIdentifier(table, conn.getPedantic()));
7164  queryBuf.append(" FROM ");
7165  queryBuf.append(StringUtils.quoteIdentifier(catalogStr, conn.getPedantic()));
7166  if (with_where) {
7167  queryBuf.append(" WHERE");
7168  queryBuf.append(whereBuf.toString());
7169  }
7170 
7171  results = stmt.executeQuery(queryBuf.toString());
7172 
7173  while (results.next()) {
7174  if (with_where || rsFields.contains(results.getString("Field"))) {
7175  TypeDescriptor typeDesc = new TypeDescriptor(results.getString("Type"), results.getString("Null"));
7176  byte[][] rowVal = new byte[8][];
7177  // SCOPE is not used
7178  rowVal[0] = null;
7179  // COLUMN_NAME
7180  rowVal[1] = results.getBytes("Field");
7181  // DATA_TYPE
7182  rowVal[2] = Short.toString(typeDesc.dataType).getBytes();
7183  // TYPE_NAME
7184  rowVal[3] = s2b(typeDesc.typeName);
7185  // COLUMN_SIZE
7186  rowVal[4] = typeDesc.columnSize == null ? null : s2b(typeDesc.columnSize.toString());
7187  // BUFFER_LENGTH
7188  rowVal[5] = s2b(Integer.toString(typeDesc.bufferLength));
7189  // DECIMAL_DIGITS
7190  rowVal[6] = typeDesc.decimalDigits == null ? null : s2b(typeDesc.decimalDigits.toString());
7191  // PSEUDO_COLUMN
7192  rowVal[7] = Integer.toString(java.sql.DatabaseMetaData.versionColumnNotPseudo).getBytes();
7193 
7194  rows.add(new ByteArrayRow(rowVal, getExceptionInterceptor()));
7195  }
7196  }
7197  }
7198  } catch (SQLException sqlEx) {
7199  if (!SQLError.SQL_STATE_BASE_TABLE_OR_VIEW_NOT_FOUND.equals(sqlEx.getSQLState())) {
7200  throw sqlEx;
7201  }
7202  } finally {
7203  if (results != null) {
7204  try {
7205  results.close();
7206  } catch (Exception ex) {
7207  ;
7208  }
7209 
7210  results = null;
7211  }
7212  }
7213 
7214  }
7215  }.doForAll();
7216  } finally {
7217  if (stmt != null) {
7218  stmt.close();
7219  }
7220  }
7221 
7222  return buildResultSet(fields, rows);
7223  }

7404  protected LocalAndReferencedColumns parseTableStatusIntoLocalAndReferencedColumns(
7405  String keysComment) throws SQLException {
7406  // keys will equal something like this:
7407  // (parent_service_id child_service_id) REFER
7408  // ds/subservices(parent_service_id child_service_id)
7409  //
7410  // simple-columned keys: (m) REFER
7411  // airline/tt(a)
7412  //
7413  // multi-columned keys : (m n) REFER
7414  // airline/vv(a b)
7415  //
7416  // parse of the string into three phases:
7417  // 1: parse the opening parentheses to determine how many results there
7418  // will be
7419  // 2: read in the schema name/table name
7420  // 3: parse the closing parentheses
7421 
7422  String columnsDelimitter = ","; // what version did this change in?
7423 
7424  char quoteChar = this.quotedId.length() == 0 ? 0 : this.quotedId
7425  .charAt(0);
7426 
7427  int indexOfOpenParenLocalColumns = StringUtils
7428  .indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(0, keysComment, "(", quoteChar,
7429  true);
7430 
7431  if (indexOfOpenParenLocalColumns == -1) {
7432  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Error parsing foreign keys definition,"
7433  + " couldn't find start of local columns list.",
7434  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
7435  }
7436 
7437  String constraintName = StringUtils.unQuoteIdentifier(
7438  keysComment.substring(0, indexOfOpenParenLocalColumns).trim(),
7439  this.conn.useAnsiQuotedIdentifiers());
7440  keysComment = keysComment.substring(indexOfOpenParenLocalColumns,
7441  keysComment.length());
7442 
7443  String keysCommentTrimmed = keysComment.trim();
7444 
7445  int indexOfCloseParenLocalColumns = StringUtils
7446  .indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(0, keysCommentTrimmed, ")",
7447  quoteChar, true);
7448 
7449  if (indexOfCloseParenLocalColumns == -1) {
7450  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Error parsing foreign keys definition,"
7451  + " couldn't find end of local columns list.",
7452  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
7453  }
7454 
7455  String localColumnNamesString = keysCommentTrimmed.substring(1,
7456  indexOfCloseParenLocalColumns);
7457 
7458  int indexOfRefer = StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(0,
7459  keysCommentTrimmed, "REFER ", this.quotedId.charAt(0), true);
7460 
7461  if (indexOfRefer == -1) {
7462  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Error parsing foreign keys definition,"
7463  + " couldn't find start of referenced tables list.",
7464  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
7465  }
7466 
7467  int indexOfOpenParenReferCol = StringUtils
7468  .indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(indexOfRefer,
7469  keysCommentTrimmed, "(", quoteChar, false);
7470 
7471  if (indexOfOpenParenReferCol == -1) {
7472  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Error parsing foreign keys definition,"
7473  + " couldn't find start of referenced columns list.",
7474  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
7475  }
7476 
7477  String referCatalogTableString = keysCommentTrimmed.substring(
7478  indexOfRefer + "REFER ".length(), indexOfOpenParenReferCol);
7479 
7480  int indexOfSlash = StringUtils.indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(0,
7481  referCatalogTableString, "/", this.quotedId.charAt(0), false);
7482 
7483  if (indexOfSlash == -1) {
7484  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Error parsing foreign keys definition,"
7485  + " couldn't find name of referenced catalog.",
7486  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
7487  }
7488 
7489  String referCatalog = StringUtils.unQuoteIdentifier(
7490  referCatalogTableString.substring(0, indexOfSlash),
7491  this.conn.useAnsiQuotedIdentifiers());
7492  String referTable = StringUtils.unQuoteIdentifier(
7493  referCatalogTableString.substring(indexOfSlash + 1).trim(),
7494  this.conn.useAnsiQuotedIdentifiers());
7495 
7496  int indexOfCloseParenRefer = StringUtils
7497  .indexOfIgnoreCaseRespectQuotes(indexOfOpenParenReferCol,
7498  keysCommentTrimmed, ")", quoteChar, true);
7499 
7500  if (indexOfCloseParenRefer == -1) {
7501  throw SQLError.createSQLException("Error parsing foreign keys definition,"
7502  + " couldn't find end of referenced columns list.",
7503  SQLError.SQL_STATE_GENERAL_ERROR, getExceptionInterceptor());
7504  }
7505 
7506  String referColumnNamesString = keysCommentTrimmed.substring(
7507  indexOfOpenParenReferCol + 1, indexOfCloseParenRefer);
7508 
7509  List<String> referColumnsList = StringUtils.split(referColumnNamesString,
7510  columnsDelimitter, this.quotedId, this.quotedId, false);
7511  List<String> localColumnsList = StringUtils.split(localColumnNamesString,
7512  columnsDelimitter, this.quotedId, this.quotedId, false);
7513 
7514  return new LocalAndReferencedColumns(localColumnsList,
7515  referColumnsList, constraintName, referCatalog, referTable);
7516  }

7532  this.conn.getServerCharacterEncoding(), this.conn

7774  public boolean supportsConvert(int fromType, int toType)
7775  throws SQLException {
7776  switch (fromType) {
7777  /*
7778  * The char/binary types can be converted to pretty much anything.
7779  */
7780  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7781  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7782  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7783  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7784  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7785  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7786 
7787  switch (toType) {
7788  case java.sql.Types.DECIMAL:
7789  case java.sql.Types.NUMERIC:
7790  case java.sql.Types.REAL:
7791  case java.sql.Types.TINYINT:
7792  case java.sql.Types.SMALLINT:
7793  case java.sql.Types.INTEGER:
7794  case java.sql.Types.BIGINT:
7795  case java.sql.Types.FLOAT:
7796  case java.sql.Types.DOUBLE:
7797  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7798  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7799  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7800  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7801  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7802  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7803  case java.sql.Types.OTHER:
7804  case java.sql.Types.DATE:
7805  case java.sql.Types.TIME:
7806  case java.sql.Types.TIMESTAMP:
7807  return true;
7808 
7809  default:
7810  return false;
7811  }
7812 
7813  /*
7814  * We don't handle the BIT type yet.
7815  */
7816  case java.sql.Types.BIT:
7817  return false;
7818 
7819  /*
7820  * The numeric types. Basically they can convert among themselves, and
7821  * with char/binary types.
7822  */
7823  case java.sql.Types.DECIMAL:
7824  case java.sql.Types.NUMERIC:
7825  case java.sql.Types.REAL:
7826  case java.sql.Types.TINYINT:
7827  case java.sql.Types.SMALLINT:
7828  case java.sql.Types.INTEGER:
7829  case java.sql.Types.BIGINT:
7830  case java.sql.Types.FLOAT:
7831  case java.sql.Types.DOUBLE:
7832 
7833  switch (toType) {
7834  case java.sql.Types.DECIMAL:
7835  case java.sql.Types.NUMERIC:
7836  case java.sql.Types.REAL:
7837  case java.sql.Types.TINYINT:
7838  case java.sql.Types.SMALLINT:
7839  case java.sql.Types.INTEGER:
7840  case java.sql.Types.BIGINT:
7841  case java.sql.Types.FLOAT:
7842  case java.sql.Types.DOUBLE:
7843  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7844  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7845  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7846  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7847  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7848  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7849  return true;
7850 
7851  default:
7852  return false;
7853  }
7854 
7855  /* MySQL doesn't support a NULL type. */
7856  case java.sql.Types.NULL:
7857  return false;
7858 
7859  /*
7860  * With this driver, this will always be a serialized object, so the
7861  * char/binary types will work.
7862  */
7863  case java.sql.Types.OTHER:
7864 
7865  switch (toType) {
7866  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7867  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7868  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7869  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7870  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7871  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7872  return true;
7873 
7874  default:
7875  return false;
7876  }
7877 
7878  /* Dates can be converted to char/binary types. */
7879  case java.sql.Types.DATE:
7880 
7881  switch (toType) {
7882  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7883  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7884  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7885  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7886  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7887  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7888  return true;
7889 
7890  default:
7891  return false;
7892  }
7893 
7894  /* Time can be converted to char/binary types */
7895  case java.sql.Types.TIME:
7896 
7897  switch (toType) {
7898  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7899  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7900  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7901  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7902  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7903  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7904  return true;
7905 
7906  default:
7907  return false;
7908  }
7909 
7910  /*
7911  * Timestamp can be converted to char/binary types and date/time types
7912  * (with loss of precision).
7913  */
7914  case java.sql.Types.TIMESTAMP:
7915 
7916  switch (toType) {
7917  case java.sql.Types.CHAR:
7918  case java.sql.Types.VARCHAR:
7919  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARCHAR:
7920  case java.sql.Types.BINARY:
7921  case java.sql.Types.VARBINARY:
7922  case java.sql.Types.LONGVARBINARY:
7923  case java.sql.Types.TIME:
7924  case java.sql.Types.DATE:
7925  return true;
7926 
7927  default:
7928  return false;
7929  }
7930 
7931  /* We shouldn't get here! */
7932  default:
7933  return false; // not sure
7934  }
7935  }
